{"lemma":"تِباعِ","slug":"تِباعِ","root":"ت.ب.ع","root_slug":"ت-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3726"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of تَابِع (tābiʕ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of تَابِع (tābiʕ)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَابَعَ (tābaʕa) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3726","headword_ar":"تِبَاعٌ","root":"tbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaAbaEapN","text_ar":"مُتَابَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEa","text_ar":"تَابَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wilaA='N","text_ar":"وِلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a consecution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succession, of one to the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona A^amorayoni","text_ar":"بَيْنَ اَمْرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between two things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making consecutive, successive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterrupted, in its progressions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gradations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 6]. (S, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEuwA bayona AlHaj~i wAlEumorapi","text_ar":"تَابِعُوا بَيْنَ الحَجِّ والعُمْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make ye a consecution between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~","text_ar":"حجّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emrp","text_ar":"عمرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make ye the performance of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~","text_ar":"حجّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emrp","text_ar":"عمرة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be consecutive"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when ye perform the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~","text_ar":"حجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then perform ye the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emrp","text_ar":"عمرة"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when ye perform the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Emrp","text_ar":"عمرة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then perform ye the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj~","text_ar":"حجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when ye perform either of these, then perform ye after it the other, without any length of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but the former [meaning] is the more obvious. (Marginal note in a copy of the Jámi'-es-Sagheer of Es-Suyootee.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbiEo bayonanaA wabayonahumo EalaY AlxayoraAti","text_ar":"تَابِعْ بَيْنَنَا وَبَيْنَهُمْ عَلَى الخَيْرَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thou us to be followers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imitators, of them in excellencies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE AlA^agaAniY~a","text_ar":"تابع الاَغَانِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sang songs consecutively, successively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterruptedly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jr","text_ar":"جر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE A_isoqaATahu","text_ar":"تابع اـِسْقَاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to fall, fall down, drop, drop down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tumble down, in consecutive portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantities"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sqT","text_ar":"سقط"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AasoqATahu","text_ar":"اَسْقاطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE Alfarasu","text_ar":"تابع الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaroYa","text_ar":"الجَرْىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse prosecuted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued, the course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running, uninterruptedly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaba","text_ar":"هَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yataAbiEu AlHadiyva","text_ar":"هُوَ يَتَابِعُ الحَدِيثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He carries on the narrative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, by consecutive progressions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterruptedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as Z says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pursues it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carries it on, well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also a similar phrase in what here follows.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE Alqawosa","text_ar":"تابع القَوْسَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trimmed, the bow well, giving to each part thereof what was its due."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Skr says that the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuwbiEa baroyuhaA","text_ar":"تُوبِعَ بَرْيُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", used by Aboo-Kebeer El-Hudhalee in describing a bow, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trimming, of which has been executed with uniformity, part after part."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence, (TA,) the saying of Abu-l-Wákid ElLeythee, (S, TA,) in a trad., (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEonaA AlA^aEomaAla","text_ar":"تَابَعْنَا الاَعْمَالَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falamo najido $ayoy^FA A^abolaga fiY Talabi AlA=xirapi mina Alz~uhodi fiY","text_ar":"فَلَمْ نَجِدْ شَيْيًا اَبْلَغَ فِى طَلَبِ الا=خِرَةِ مِنَ الزُّهْدِ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have practised works with diligence, and acquired a sound knowledge of them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we have not found anything more efficacious in the pursuit of the blessings of the world to come than abstinence in respect of the enjoyments of the present world."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, * TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE Eamalahu","text_ar":"تابع عَمَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his work sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from defect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, S:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmahu","text_ar":"كَلَامَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his language,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbE AlmaroEaY AlA_ibila","text_ar":"تابع المَرْعَى الاـِبِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pasture fattened the camels well and thoroughly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tAbEhu EalaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"تابعهُ عَلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided, assisted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"helped, him to do the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  See also 1, where another meaning of the same phrase is mentioned, in the latter half of the paragraph. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAbaEotuhu biHaq~iY","text_ar":"تَابَعْتُهُ بِحَقِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the end of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Kr"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}